                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-286-off1594 t18270913-286-crimeloc1597"></join>. On the 20th of August, when I got up, my shoes were gone; they were safe before, on the stairs - the prisoner had lodged there about ten days.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-286-person2243">
                  CHARLES 
                  MANDER
               <interp inst="t18270913-286-person2243" type="surname" value="MANDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-286-person2243" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-286-person2243" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 20th of August I found my brother's shoes on the prisoner, as he was walking up Hampton-court; he said he was sorry for it, but he was tipsy.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I only took them while I got my own mended - I told him I had a good mind to turn thief, as his shoes were better than mine.</p>
               <p>HENRY MANDER. He did say so, but his own were not gone to be mended.</p>
